<br>
please.<br>
<br>
the rest of the report was great.  a lot of thought, some great ideas.  some are silly, some probably overpowering, but obviously a lot of effort and that is surely appreciated by all of us.  but the RAs .... <br>
<br>
you know the worst part about them is that if one of them does get used, foolish n00b skalds might be fooled into thinking it would have some potential.  at least with the current one every single person who knows what it does can easily see it is complete garbage.<br>
<br>
if you need ideas for RAs, you really only need to ask -<br>
<br>
- 60 second pulsing cumulative debuff to all magic and melee resists (same radius as thornweed field)<br>
<br>
- group 30 second hits/power/end increase<br>
<br>
- 30 second group 50% haste stacking with all other buffs<br>
<br>
- 30 second group 75-100% haste overwriting all other buffs<br>
<br>
- group 50%-100% chance all spells/attacks critical hit<br>
<br>
- self 125 point charisma buff .. 5 minute duration 15 minute timer (might need to add something this is kinda weak)<br>
<br>
- group timer reset all timed abilities (RAs, instants, etc) become useable again immediately (might be too powerful if RAs included, in which case all instants/regular spell timers reset)<br>
<br>
- 800 radius immunity remover 15 minute timer - group purge removed mez no problem can now mez again<br>
<br>
- group instantly transported to nearest friendly portal keep or border keep, handy when ambushed or being overrun by monsters - duke bimure baf's with mutilator?  BYE BYE !<br>
<br>
<br>
some of these i would not buy either, but a lot of them i would at least think about.  however none of the RAs listed in the monthly report i would even CONSIDER buying, and i have 57 points to spend.<br>
<br>
ok that's not quite true.  if the pbaoe nearsight was increased to 400 radius and the cost was reduced to under six, i would -consider- it.  it would be a tossup between empty mind and that for my next purchase, in 3 or 4 months when i've finally saved 6 points.  <br>
<br>
there is my semi-constructive criticism for the evening.<br>
<br>
<br>
Phleet<br>
